---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Smart Reactions"
  track="young-builders"
  week={9}
  phase="Phase 3: AI Projects"
  duration="60 min"
  emoji="⚡"
  objective="Combine vision, voice, and sensors to create intelligent responses"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-builder-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-builder-50 border-l-4 border-builder-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      You will integrate multiple input streams (vision, voice, sensors) into a unified AI system that makes context-aware decisions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Context Map (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Draw a diagram: what if Reachy has BOTH a voice command AND a visual input at the same time? How should it prioritize? Design your priority system.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Multimodal AI (30 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Build the combined system. Test it with scenarios that require weighing multiple inputs. What happens when inputs conflict?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Capstone Prep (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Start designing your Week 10 project. What problem will Reachy solve? What inputs will it need?</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># smart_reactions.py — Week 9: Young Builders
import random
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def say(self, msg): print(f"🔊 {msg}"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def wave(self): print("👋 *waves*"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def set_emotion(self, e): print(f"😊 *{e}*"); time.sleep(0.3)
    def move_head(self, yaw=0): print(f"👀 yaw={yaw}°"); time.sleep(0.3)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()

def get_context():
    """Simulate a full multi-sensor snapshot."""
    return {
        "vision":  random.choice(["person", "empty", "bright_object", None]),
        "voice":   random.choice(["hello", "help", "dance", None]),
        "battery": random.randint(15, 100),
        "sound":   random.randint(0, 100),
        "time_of_day": random.choice(["morning", "afternoon", "evening"]),
    }

def smart_respond(ctx):
    """Multi-modal decision engine."""
    print(f"\n📊 Context: {ctx}")

    # Priority 1: Safety
    if ctx["battery"] < 20:
        robot.say("Low battery — I need to charge soon!")
        return

    # Priority 2: Direct voice command
    if ctx["voice"] == "help":
        robot.set_emotion("concerned")
        robot.say("I heard you need help! What can I do?")
        return

    # Priority 3: Vision + Voice combined
    if ctx["vision"] == "person" and ctx["voice"] == "hello":
        robot.set_emotion("happy")
        robot.wave()
        robot.say(f"Good {ctx['time_of_day']}! Happy to see you!")
        return

    # Priority 4: Vision only
    if ctx["vision"] == "person":
        robot.set_emotion("curious")
        robot.move_head(yaw=15)
        robot.say("I notice someone nearby.")
        return

    # Priority 5: Voice only
    if ctx["voice"] == "dance":
        robot.say("Dance time!")
        return

    # Default: ambient awareness
    if ctx["time_of_day"] == "morning":
        robot.say("Good morning! Ready for a new day.")
    elif ctx["sound"] > 80:
        robot.say("It's quite noisy around here.")
    else:
        robot.set_emotion("neutral")

print("🤖 Smart Reactions System\n")
for i in range(5):
    print(f"=== Scenario {i+1} ===")
    context = get_context()
    smart_respond(context)
    time.sleep(0.5)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 How did you decide the priority order? What are the trade-offs?</p></div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What's one scenario where your system would make the wrong decision?</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 Multi-modal AI (combining vision + language + sensors) is exactly what modern AI assistants do. Your child is thinking like an AI systems engineer!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
